// T039 (T059): malformed NSL → exit non-zero + an error
// diagnostic on stderr (Q1 strict-refusal per Session 2026-05-05;
// FR-012 atomic refusal).
//
// Input is `module foo {` with NO closing brace — the parser hits
// EOF while expecting `}` and emits a parse-error diagnostic.

// RUN: echo 'module foo {' | not nsl-fmt --stdin 2>&1 | FileCheck %s
// CHECK: error
